# Package: `@excalidraw/math`

## Role

- **Numeric / geometric primitives**: points, vectors, lines, curves, ranges, angles — types and functions for 2D editor math.
- **No React** — library code only.

## Dependencies

- MAY import `@excalidraw/common`.
- MUST NOT import `@excalidraw/element`, `@excalidraw/excalidraw`, or `@excalidraw/utils`.

## Conventions

- Use and expose shared types from this package (e.g. **`Point`**, **`Radians`**, **`LocalPoint`**) rather than ad-hoc `{ x, y }` at call sites that cross package boundaries. See `packages/math/src/types.ts`.
- Prefer immutable-style helpers (return new values) unless an existing API is explicitly mutating.
- Keep functions deterministic and side-effect free where possible (easier to test under `packages/math/tests/`).

## How to verify

- `yarn --cwd ./packages/math build:esm` (or `yarn build:math` from repo root).
- `yarn test:app --watch=false` with a path filter on `packages/math/tests` when practical.
- If math types feed into `element` / `excalidraw`: also run `yarn test:typecheck`.
